# рџљЂ Installation

## 1пёЏвѓЈ Clone Repo

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/dotfiles.git

cd dotfiles
```

---

## 2пёЏвѓЈ Run Installer

```bash
chmod +x install.sh

./install.sh
```

---

# вљ™ install.sh Guide

The installer:

* Installs official Arch packages
* Installs AUR packages
* Skips missing packages safely
* Copies configs
* Restores user environment

---

# рџ“њ Example install.sh

```bash
#!/bin/bash

GREEN='\033[0;32m'
YELLOW='\033[1;33m'
NC='\033[0m'

install_pkg() {
    local manager=$1
    local pkg=$2

    if [[ -z "$pkg" || "$pkg" =~ ^# ]]; then
        return
    fi

    if $manager -Si "$pkg" &>/dev/null; then
        echo -e "${GREEN}[INSTALL]${NC} $pkg"
        $manager -S --needed --noconfirm "$pkg"
    else
        echo -e "${YELLOW}[SKIP]${NC} $pkg not found"
    fi
}

echo "Installing official packages..."

while read -r pkg; do
    install_pkg sudo\ pacman "$pkg"
done < packages/arch.txt

echo "Installing AUR packages..."

while read -r pkg; do
    install_pkg yay "$pkg"
done < packages/aur.txt

echo "Copying configs..."

mkdir -p ~/.config

cp -r hypr ~/.config/
cp -r i3 ~/.config/
cp -r rofi ~/.config/
cp -r nvim ~/.config/

cp terminal/zsh/.zshrc ~/
cp terminal/starship/starship.toml ~/.config/

echo "Done."
```

---

# рџ›Ў Security Notes

Never upload:

* `.ssh/id_*`
* API keys
* `.env`
* Tokens
* Secrets

Use:

```text
.gitignore
```

for private files.

